China resources
Hi.

We have plans to run our application in China region and would like to have some information about possible issues there.

From what I already got - we can't have simple VPN from our EU to CH region. Is it correct?

Our infrastructure includes;

a) Maven to build Java code and Docker images;
b) Docker images to be saved in private registry (CBCcom? As Docker Hub will be too slow);
c) Packer to build AMIs adding Docker images inside;
d) Terraform to update ELB stack with new instances from Packer's AMIs.

As we seem will have EU <=> CN connection issues - currently, we plan to move Jenkins CI to CN instance.

But there are other issues as well:

1. `apt-get install maven` took about 2-3 hours to download all dependencies;
2. `mvn build` hangs on downloading Maven/Java dependencies;
3. an `ssh` connection to EC2 in CN too slow - can't even type commands (I'm writing them in a text editor, and then copy-paste to the terminal).

That's only a few I found at this moment (working from Kiev, not in CH yet).

Maybe somebody had a similar task and have some solution there?

Thanks in advance.

Edited by: setevoy on Dec 12, 2016 1:45 AM

Edited by: setevoy on Dec 12, 2016 1:46 AM

