PHP uploading document with cURL
Hello. I have the example Java upload working. I am mapping that over to PHP but getting an odd error, "The request signature we calculated does not match the signature you provided"
This is odd because the upload URL is verbatim what was sent back to me from initiateDocumentVersionUpload. The PHP approach used is below. Is there a PHP reference example?

$contentType = 'application/octet-stream';
$xx = $workDocsClient->initiateDocumentVersionUpload(
	array ("ParentFolderId" => $rootFolderId, 
		'ContentType' => $contentType, 'Name' => $docName)  );
$meta = $xx;
$docId = $meta;
$latestVersionMeta = $meta;
$docVersionId = $latestVersionMeta;
$uploadMeta = $xx;
$uploadUrl = $uploadMeta;
$headers = array("Content-Type" => $contentType,
	"x-amz-server-side-encryption"  => "AES256" );	
$postData = array ( 'file_contents' => curl_file_create ($docPath) );
$ch = curl_init ($uploadUrl);
curl_setopt ($ch, CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST, "PUT");
curl_setopt ($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, $headers);
curl_setopt ($ch, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, $postData);
curl_setopt ($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, 1);
$result = curl_exec ($ch);
curl_close ($ch);
var_dump($result);
// WE SEE THE SIGNATURE ERROR MESSAGE HERE.
// THE NEXT CALL FAILS BECAUSE THE FILE IS NOT UPLOADED ABOVE.
$workDocsClient->updateDocumentVersion(
   array ( 'DocumentId' => $docId, 'VersionId' => $docVersionId) );


Bill

Re: PHP uploading document with cURL
I bagged cURL and this worked. Hope it helps others.

Bill


	$postData = file_get_contents($docPath);
	// use key 'http' even if you send the request to https://...
	$options = array(
		'http' => array(
				'header'  => "Content-Type: $contentType\r\nx-amz-server-side-encryption: AES256\r\n",
				'method'  => 'PUT',
				'content' => $postData,
		),
	);
	$context  = stream_context_create($options);
	$result = file_get_contents($uploadUrl, false, $context);

