AWS Workdocs API & PHP: preview doesn't load until browser refresh
I've run into a problem with uploading document via the API that I can't seem to solve.  The file uploads fine and I'm able to see it in my directory.  I can click the file and it looks like it goes to the detail.  But until I refresh the browser, the preview doesn't load.  I have tried all of the following:


uploading a document manually to this folder.  The preview shows immediately
uploading a text file via API.  No preview until refresh.
uploading a word document via API.  No preview until refresh.
comparing all the fields on a manual document against an API loaded document.  Only the creator is different.
comparing all the fields on an API loaded document before and after the preview is generated.  All fields appear to be the same.


Here is my code:

        // this is just a wrapper around the execution of calls to workdocs
        $workdocs = new AWS_WorkDocs_Helper();
        // these are all word documents
        $content_type = "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document";
        $params = [
            'ContentType' => $content_type,
            'Name' => $filename,
            'ParentFolderId' => $parent_folder,
        ];
        $results = $workdocs->execute_command('InitiateDocumentVersionUpload', $params);
        $upload_url = $results;
        $document_id = $results;
        $document_version = $results;
        $signed_headers_ex = $results;
        $signed_headers = [];
        // change array value to key: value
        foreach ($signed_headers_ex as $key => $value)
            $signed_headers[] = $key . ': ' . $value;
        // a PUT call to upload the file contents.  See below
        $cur_helper = new CURL_Helper();
        if (!$cur_helper->upload_workdocs_file($upload_url, $path, $signed_headers))
            dd($cur_helper->error);

        $params = [
            'DocumentId' => $document_id,
            'VersionId' => $document_version,
        ];
        $workdocs->execute_command('UpdateDocumentVersion', $params);

class CURL_Helper
{
    public $error;
    public $response;

    public function upload_workdocs_file($url, $filename, $signed_headers)
    {
        $file_contents = file_get_contents($filename);
        $options = array(
            CURLOPT_URL => $url,
            CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST => "PUT",
            CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => $file_contents,
            CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => $signed_headers
        );
        return $this->post_request($options);
    }

    protected function post_request($options)
    {
        $curl = curl_init();
        curl_setopt_array($curl, $options);
        $this->response = curl_exec($curl);
        $this->error = curl_error($curl);
        curl_close($curl);
        return $this->error == '';
    }
}

